# The IB Omniscience Portal & Programming Sandbox

Welcome to my personal development workspace! This repository is a dual-purpose environment where I am actively building out **The Ultimate Automated IB Omniscience Portal** while simultaneously working through intermediate Python programming labs and software architecture exercises.

The project bridges local hardware configurations (like Mac and iPad sync states) with structural programming logic to automate student workflows, data analytics, and active recall streams.

---

## 🏛️ System Architecture: The Omniscience Portal

The core ecosystem functions as a unified desktop application where modules handle runtime control handoffs, share dynamic local JSON databases, and concurrently monitor file-system modifications via background daemons.

### Core Architecture Rules Applied:

* **Dynamic Path Alignment (`os.path`):** Zero hardcoded root directories. Every component automatically maps its data streams relative to its execution location, preventing breaks across different development machines.
* **Non-Blocking Multithreading:** The background watchdog filesystem listener is decoupled from the user-facing CLI loops inside an isolated daemon thread so it runs silently without hanging the UI.
* **Module Handshakes:** Sub-modules don't step on each other's data footprints. They interact through structured import gates and pre-verified functional interfaces.

```
                  [ workspace.py (Master Hub) ]
                                |
         +----------------------+----------------------+
         | (Launches Daemon)                           | (Menu Navigation)
         v                                             v
[ watchdog_daemon.py ]                        [ Core Feature Engines ]
         |                                             |
         | (Auto-intercepts iPad Notes)                +--> note_processor.py (Gemini AI)
         v                                             +--> spanish_suite.py (Vocab Matrix)
[ assignment_planner.py ] <-----+                     +--> ia_plotter.py (Matplotlib)
                                |                      +--> ib_grade_tracker.py (Analytics)
                                +----------------------+--> formula_bank.py (STEM Search)

```

