## 📁 Component Breakdown

### 🛰️ Automated Framework Extensions

#### 1. The Master Workspace Hub (`workspace.py`)

Acts as the central router and runtime shell for the ecosystem. Upon booting, it detaches the background synchronization worker into an isolated daemon thread before spinning up an optimized, persistent execution menu to pass control to individual modules.

#### 2. AI Note-Processor & Flashcard Engine (`note_processor.py`)

An automated active-recall pipeline powered by the official **Google GenAI SDK** and the `gemini-2.5-flash` model. It ingests raw textual notes, enforces a strict, custom serialization string format via LLM prompts, and parses the returned stream into a clean `flashcards.json` schema.

#### 3. Linguistic Spanish B Synthesis Suite (`spanish_suite.py`)

Organizes and handles student foreign language vocabularies mapped to the five official IB Prescribed Themes. Features localized database initialization fallbacks, domain verification rules to block invalid target entries, and a randomized translation test engine.

#### 4. IA Data-Logger & Vector Plotter (`ia_plotter.py`)

A data analysis utility built using `matplotlib` to support Internal Assessment lab reporting. It handles matrix-to-float list comprehensions, checks vector dimension symmetry to guarantee 1:1 coordinates, and purges system-illegal string characters to safely export high-density charts as `.png` files.

#### 5. Autonomous iCloud Watchdog Daemon (`watchdog_daemon.py`)

A continuous system observer powered by the `watchdog` api. Locked onto local iCloud storage containers, it traps file-system write modifications the moment an asset lands from an external device (like an iPad), isolates temporary system locks, and injects clean scheduler records directly into the planner engine.

### 🗃️ Core Student Utilities & Analytics

#### 6. Academic Assignment Planner (`assignment_planner.py`)

A task management manager layered with data persistence. It monitors deadlines, filters incoming entries to reject duplicates, and normalizes inputs to guarantee consistent runtime states during cross-module data injection.

#### 7. IB Grade Tracker (`ib_grade_tracker.py`)

An evaluation engine processing performance matrices against strict conditional boundary scales. It translates numeric percentages into official grade classifications (1-7) and dynamically computes cumulative core bonus tracks.

#### 8. STEM Formula Vault (`formula_bank.py`)

A fast indexing library with automated database seeding. It allows keyword extraction and custom text normalization to sort, index, and query foundational math and physics calculations.

